Property worth Sh5 million was reduced to ash after two boutiques were on Thursday gutted by fire in Limuru town, Kiambu county. One of the boutiques was a tailoring shop which made uniform for both primary and secondary schools.  The boutiques were next to Limuru open-air cereals market. Boutique owner Benard Ndung’u said uniforms, fabrics, new clothes and shoes were destroyed. “We were called by watchmen and told our shop is on fire. It was around 1am. ” he said. Ndung’u, who is also a DJ, said his mixer, speakers and laptops were destroyed. The other trader - Joel Muiruri - said he had recently imported new clothes and shoes from Dubai.      